The department has accused the two Afrikaans medium schools of refusing to accommodate English speaking pupils. JOHANNESBURG Two Pretoria high schools served the Gauteng Department of Education with a court interdict late on Monday night regarding language policies.The matter will be heard in the Pretoria High Court on Wednesday morning.The department has accused the two Afrikaans medium schools of refusing to accommodate English speaking pupils.Spokesperson Oupa Bodibe says, We ve been engaging the schools to see if they can t accommodate some of the parents that are actually living closer but are being excluded because the schools are either mostly Afrikaans or they have only one classroom teaching English. (Edited by Leeto M Khoza)